Here's the nuclear option:

```js
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET,POST,PUT,DELETE,OPTIONS');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type,Authorization');

  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {
    return res.sendStatus(200);
  }
  next();
});
```

**Put this BEFORE all your routes.**

This will work for your demo tomorrow.

---

**One honest warning though:** `*` means anyone can hit your API. For a demo that's totally fine. But after the demo, go back and lock it down to your actual frontend URL.

